HEADWORD: Absterge
<hw>Ab*sterge</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>abstergere</ets>, <ets>abstersum</ets>; <ets>ab</ets>,
<ets>abs</ets> + <ets>tergere</ets> to wipe. Cf. F
<ets>absterger</ets>.]</ety> <def>To make clean by wiping; to wipe away;
to cleanse; hence, to purge.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Quincy.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

